  						<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF FURIOUS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;56</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;9 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;56 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline the warrior will automatically riposte every attack landed on them by the opponent they are facing.  This discipline lasts for 9 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WEIGHTED AXE</span><b>, By Emperior quinn</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>One word, weighted axe, ok that's 2 words. But keep in mind that repost does not take the delay in consideration so your 44/150 weapon becomes 44/0 for 14 seconds.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>QUESTION...</span><b>, By Balurik</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>When a mobs is enraged, it is possible to use this disc to re re-riposte the mobs,
or will it make zone crash due to riposte loop?<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YOU WILL ONLY ATTACK THE MOB ON YOU.</span><b>, By Konaan</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>i've done this many times, i attack a hg that a big group is killing just for fun, and when the riposte i get no dmg report, or miss report, so i think they only attack who they hace targeted. so maybe if you have 5 mobs attacking you, you will only attack one back. if this is so some cheats could be used. say a warrior throws this skill on and someone in a duel with him attacks him with two fine steel daggers, they will do crap dmg but give him like 20 more attacks... someone else please confirm this.

<p>Konaan Corpselayer
<p>30 barbarian warrior
<p>Forces of Rage<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IT DOESN'T WORK LIKE THAT IN REALITY</span><b>, By Dagrak darkgiant</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>You cannot riposte missed attacks.  You have to block 1 attack which would land and counter attack.  The counter attack will miss or hit like a regular swing.

<p>You can riposte anything in any direction your facing!  You can riposte attacks from the back but you will not counter.  You will get a message saying you cannot see your target. If they are in your sight and in range you can riposte up to 3 monsters which is the max amount of melee mobs that can be attacking you at once.

<p>This is a good disciple because you are virtually invulnerable to melee.  You cannot riposte a spell...

Another note, Weighted Axe is 45/150 or something... There's another weapon called the Oggok Cleaver which is 44/66 or so.  I would never use the Weighted Axe unless in a test because it's such a crappy and useless weapon.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>THIS IS A GREAT SKILL...</span><b>, By Rennol tarew marr</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>This is what you want to use in Karnor's Castle or someplace where stuff agro's really easily.  If the puller pulls too much just run out in front of the group so that everything will stop and attack you.  Now, switch to your best damage weapon (A weighted axe works great for this, don't laugh:P).

<p>So at this point you have about 3-6 mobs all pissed off and hitting you about 2-3 times per round (3.0 seconds maybe) with a 45 dmg weapon in your hand.  Now activate this discipline and mow through them until its over and then switch back to normal weapons :).

<p>I can't even begin to imagine the damage it would generate with enough mobs attacking you from the front and a huge weapon, heh.  Figure like 15 attacks per round from 3-6 mobs and then 4 rounds for the duration and you get 60 free swings in a row, heh.  This would be great while beserk maybe too, if you could live that long :P  Too bad you cant use 2 disciplines at a time, Furious + Mighty Strike while beserk would be a sight to see :)<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
